import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.boxplot(x='Species', y='Body_Mass__g_', data=data)
    chart.set_title('What is the distribution of body mass across different species?', wrap=True)
    chart.legend(title='Species', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='Beak_Length__mm_', y='Beak_Depth__mm_', hue='Species', style='Sex')
    plt.title('How does beak length vary with beak depth?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Species & Sex')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_flipper_length = data.groupby('Species')['Flipper_Length__mm_'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Species', y='Flipper_Length__mm_', data=avg_flipper_length)
    plt.title('What is the average flipper length for each species?', wrap=True)
    chart.set(xlabel='Species', ylabel='Average Flipper Length (mm)')
    plt.legend(title='Species', loc='upper right', labels=avg_flipper_length['Species'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
